	<h2>National Blueway Designation </h2>
	<p>
		The National Blueways System was launched by the U.S. Department of the Interior in 2012 to recognize and support America’s great rivers and watersheds that are prized for their life-sustaining contributions to the human, wildlife and plant communities dependent on them. The program emphasizes a holistic “headwaters to mouth” approach to river-basin stewardship and encourages cohesive, watershed-wide partnerships. Among the benefits of Blueways designation is the development of inter-agency agreements that would allow for the alignment of priorities and funding across federal and state partners.  The Coalition has created a subcommittee to develop a proposal to designate the Delaware River Watershed as a National Blueway.  For more on how National Blueway designation could benefit the Delaware River Watershed, click here (hyperlink to the Blueways website -- http://www.doi.gov/americasgreatoutdoors/whatwedo/rivers/Rivers-National-Blueway-System.cfm) 
